7.0H PRO UPDATE INFORMATION

This release contains lots of bug fixes, PLUS file tagging in the file
open prompt (see README.DOC or ME.HLP).

This release now allows for the transfer of network license info via
the NETXFER.EXE utility.

If you are using VCS support, then you should run VCS_INST in order to
update your menus with new features.

If you are wondering why we are not using RTPATCH on this update file,
it is simple.  There have been 7.00, a, b, c, d, e and f releases.
That's a lot of patch variants, making  for a pretty big file.  In
addition, our experience with using patch software on a product as
complex as Multi-Edit has not been good.  There are just too many
opportunities for people to modify the source code, or menus, etc.
Every time we release a patch update that patches more than a couple of
files, we get DOZENS of individual messages asking us if we could email
this file or that file because the patch didn't work right.  That was
just during the beta cycle.  We've now shipped thousands of copies of
7.0x.

Thanks for your support.
